full
Homonym Number:
Word Class: adjective
Sense Number:
Definition:construed with blast, bore, lick, out, split, swing, to form phrasal adverbs with the sense `at full speed'; `energetically'; `flat out', of speed, activity of any kind (cf OED FULL 9c)
Origin: [none]
Register:
Register 2:
Domain: [none]
Region: [none]
See:
Pronunciation:
Notes: Constr. omits prepos at or in: full speed can also be used adverbially this way. All have been in common coll use since at least the 1930s.  (cf EDD drive 13. full drive w Yks, Nhp `he went along, full drive, to use a common express for walking or running' 11. full used as an intensive in phr -bang, -bet, -split [but not -nit])
